The paper discusses the computational complexity of approximating maximum a posteriori inference in sum-product networks, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI) as well as statistical inference (cs.IT). The paper also presents algorithms and empirical analysis, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of sum-product networks in practical applications, which could potentially fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
